				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Carboxymethyl cellulose (CMC) or cellulose gum is a cellulose derivative with carboxymethyl groups (-CH 2-COOH) bound to some of the hydroxyl groups of the glucopyranose monomers that make up the cellulose backbone. It is often used as its sodium salt, sodium carboxymethyl cellulose. It used to be marketed under the name Tylose. CMC is the major cellulose ether. It is used widely for the production of CMC. It appears as white, fibrous, free-flowing powder, and is used commonly as an FDA-approved disintegrant in pharmaceutical manufacturing.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">羧甲基纤维素（CMC）或纤维素胶是一种纤维素衍生物，其羧甲基基团（-CH 2-COOH）与构成纤维素骨架的吡喃葡萄糖单体的部分羟基结合。它常用的钠盐是羧甲基纤维素钠。它曾以木糖的名称在市场上销售。CMC 是主要的纤维素醚。它被广泛用于生产 CMC。它呈白色、纤维状、自由流动的粉末，通常用作 FDA 批准的药品生产中的崩解剂。</common:generalComment>
			<sumFormula>-CH 2-COOH</sumFormula>
